This is the actual hand written read me by conner for later running and notes

much of the project was done by copying edje electronics video called "how to run yolo object detection models on the raspberry pi"
and also "how to train yolo object detection models in google colab (yolo11,yolov8, yolov5)"


to start up the code:
1. go to the yolo folder
2. run: source venv/bin/activate
3. run: python detect_goosev2.py --model=goose11s_ncnn_model --source=picamera0 --resolution=1280x720
or for usb camera: python detect_goosev2.py --model=goose11s_ncnn_model --source=usb0 --resolution=1280x720